@{
    Layout = "_DocsLayout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Production deployment";
    ViewData["NavActive"] = "production";
    ViewData["DocsActive"] = "production";
    ViewData["Description"] = "Run Authly in production with an external, hardened PostgreSQL: bind-mounted data, custom postgresql.conf, pg_hba.conf rules, Traefik TLS, resource limits, and the gotchas that bite on a first real deployment.";
}

<p class="eyebrow">Getting started</p>
<h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Production deployment.</h1>
<p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">A hardened, real-world setup: a dedicated PostgreSQL with a bind-mounted data directory and a tuned <code>postgresql.conf</code>, the Authly app behind Traefik with TLS, resource limits, and per-container networking. This is the reference for a production host — for a zero-config local run, see <a class="text-primary hover:underline" href="/docs/self-host">Self-host with Docker</a> instead.</p>

<div class="mt-4 card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-primary text-sm">
    <i data-lucide="info" class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
    <div>Replace every <code>&lt;placeholder&gt;</code> below with your own values: <code>&lt;base-path&gt;</code> (host directory for persistent data), <code>&lt;your-network&gt;</code> / <code>&lt;*-ip&gt;</code> (Docker network + static IPs), <code>&lt;your-domain&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;your-subnet&gt;</code>.</div>
</div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 1 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">1. Directory structure</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Postgres data and config live on the host so they survive container recreation and image upgrades.</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>&lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/
├── data/                        <span class="tok-com"># Postgres data files (bind mount)</span>
│   └── pgdata/
│       ├── pg_hba.conf          <span class="tok-com"># Client authentication rules</span>
│       └── postgresql.conf      <span class="tok-com"># Auto-generated (managed by Postgres)</span>
├── postgresql.conf              <span class="tok-com"># Custom config (mounted into container)</span>
└── initdb/                      <span class="tok-com"># *.sql scripts run on first init only</span></code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 2 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">2. Environment variables</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Add these to a <code>.env</code> file next to your Compose files.</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code><span class="tok-com">#============= POSTGRES ================</span>
POSTGRES_USER=&lt;username&gt;
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=&lt;password&gt;
POSTGRES_DB=&lt;database-name&gt;

<span class="tok-com">#============= AUTHLY ==================</span>
ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Production
APP_PORT=8080
ENCRYPTION_KEY=&lt;generate: openssl rand -base64 32&gt;
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://&lt;your-domain&gt;
RETENTION_LOGIN_HISTORY_DAYS=90
RETENTION_AUDIT_DAYS=365
WEBSITE_ENABLED=false
AUTHLY_VERSION=&lt;image-tag&gt;
AUTHLY_DOMAIN=&lt;authly-subdomain&gt;
AUTHLY_DOMAIN_PORT=8080</code></div>
<div class="mt-3 card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-primary text-sm">
    <i data-lucide="globe" class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
    <div><code>WEBSITE_ENABLED</code> is <strong>off by default</strong> — in production only the IdP/console (login, OIDC, admin) is served and the marketing/landing routes redirect to the admin console.</div>
</div>

<h3 class="font-display text-base font-bold mt-6 mb-2">Want the public marketing website too?</h3>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Turn it on by either setting <code>WEBSITE_ENABLED=true</code> in <code>.env</code> (the <code>authly</code> service reads it via <code>Website__Enabled=${WEBSITE_ENABLED:-false}</code>), or by hard-setting the env var directly on the <code>authly</code> service:</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>  authly:
    environment:
      - Website__Enabled=true</code></div>
<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">The flag is read once at startup, so recreate the container after changing it: <code>docker compose up -d authly</code>.</p>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 3 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">3. docker-compose.yml</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">The base file just pins images; everything host-specific goes in the override (next section).</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:17
  authly:
    image: abhiraheja/authly:${AUTHLY_VERSION}</code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 4 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">4. docker-compose.override.yml</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Resource limits, hardening, bind mounts, healthchecks, and Traefik routing.</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>  postgres:
    container_name: postgres
    restart: unless-stopped
    stop_grace_period: 1m
    shm_size: 256mb
    security_opt:
      - no-new-privileges:true
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: ${POSTGRES_USER}
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}
      POSTGRES_DB: ${POSTGRES_DB}
      PGDATA: /var/lib/postgresql/data/pgdata
    ports:
      - "127.0.0.1:5432:5432"
    volumes:
      - &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/data:/var/lib/postgresql/data
      - &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/postgresql.conf:/etc/postgresql.conf:ro
      - &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/initdb:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d:ro
    command: ["postgres", "-c", "config_file=/etc/postgresql.conf"]
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "pg_isready -U $${POSTGRES_USER} -d $${POSTGRES_DB}"]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 5
      start_period: 30s
    cpus: "2.0"
    mem_limit: 4g
    logging:
      driver: json-file
      options:
        max-size: "10m"
        max-file: "3"
    networks:
      &lt;your-network&gt;:
        ipv4_address: &lt;postgres-ip&gt;

  authly:
    container_name: authly
    pull_policy: always
    restart: unless-stopped
    security_opt:
      - no-new-privileges:true
    environment:
      - ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=${ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT:-Production}
      - DATABASE_URL=Host=&lt;postgres-ip&gt;;Database=${POSTGRES_DB};Username=${POSTGRES_USER};Password=${POSTGRES_PASSWORD};SSL Mode=Disable;Trust Server Certificate=true
      - REDIS_URL=&lt;redis-ip&gt;:6379,password=&lt;redis-password&gt;,ssl=false,abortConnect=false
      - ENCRYPTION_KEY=${ENCRYPTION_KEY}
      - CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=${CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS:-}
      - RETENTION_LOGIN_HISTORY_DAYS=${RETENTION_LOGIN_HISTORY_DAYS:-90}
      - RETENTION_AUDIT_DAYS=${RETENTION_AUDIT_DAYS:-365}
      - WEBSITE_ENABLED=${WEBSITE_ENABLED:-false}
      - LOG_STREAM_ENDPOINT=${LOG_STREAM_ENDPOINT:-}
      - LOG_STREAM_KEY=${LOG_STREAM_KEY:-}
      - OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=${OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT:-}
    depends_on:
      postgres:
        condition: service_healthy
      redis:
        condition: service_started
    labels:
      - "traefik.enable=true"
      - "traefik.http.routers.authly.rule=Host(`${AUTHLY_DOMAIN}`)"
      - "traefik.http.routers.authly.entrypoints=websecure"
      - "traefik.http.routers.authly.tls=true"
      - "traefik.http.routers.authly.tls.certresolver=le"
      - "traefik.http.routers.authly.service=authly"
      - "traefik.http.routers.authly.middlewares=secure-headers@@file"
      - "traefik.http.services.authly.loadbalancer.server.port=${AUTHLY_DOMAIN_PORT}"
    networks:
      &lt;your-network&gt;:
        ipv4_address: &lt;authly-ip&gt;</code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 5 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">5. postgresql.conf</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Mounted at <code>&lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/postgresql.conf</code>. Values below assume ~4 GB available to the container (<code>mem_limit: 4g</code>) — tune <code>shared_buffers</code>, <code>effective_cache_size</code>, and <code>work_mem</code> to your host.</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>listen_addresses = '*'
max_connections = 100
superuser_reserved_connections = 3
shared_buffers = 1GB
effective_cache_size = 3GB
maintenance_work_mem = 256MB
work_mem = 8MB
wal_buffers = 16MB
random_page_cost = 1.1
effective_io_concurrency = 200
wal_level = replica
min_wal_size = 1GB
max_wal_size = 4GB
checkpoint_completion_target = 0.9
checkpoint_timeout = 15min
max_worker_processes = 4
max_parallel_workers = 4
max_parallel_workers_per_gather = 2
max_parallel_maintenance_workers = 2
autovacuum = on
autovacuum_max_workers = 3
autovacuum_naptime = 30s
log_destination = 'stderr'
logging_collector = off
log_min_duration_statement = 1000
log_checkpoints = on
log_connections = on
log_disconnections = on
log_lock_waits = on
log_temp_files = 0
log_line_prefix = '%m [%p] %q%u@@%d '
statement_timeout = 0
idle_in_transaction_session_timeout = 60000
timezone = 'UTC'
datestyle = 'iso, mdy'</code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 6 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">6. pg_hba.conf</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Located at <code>&lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/data/pgdata/pg_hba.conf</code>. This line lets every container on your Docker network authenticate:</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>host    all             all             &lt;your-subnet&gt;/24           scram-sha-256</code></div>
<p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Append it, then reload without restarting Postgres:</p>
<div class="mt-2 code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>echo "host all all &lt;your-subnet&gt;/24 scram-sha-256" &gt;&gt; &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/data/pgdata/pg_hba.conf
docker exec postgres psql -U &lt;username&gt; -d postgres -c "SELECT pg_reload_conf();"</code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 7 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">7. Gotchas (read before first boot)</h2>
<div class="space-y-3">
    <div class="card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500 text-sm">
        <i data-lucide="folder-tree" class="size-4 text-amber-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
        <div><strong>Config must be a file, not a directory.</strong> If the host path doesn't exist, Docker creates a <em>directory</em> at the mount point. Create the file <em>before</em> <code>docker compose up</code> — write your <code>postgresql.conf</code> first, then start.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500 text-sm">
        <i data-lucide="file-cog" class="size-4 text-amber-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
        <div><strong>Config mount path.</strong> The official <code>postgres:17</code> image has no <code>/etc/postgresql/</code> directory. Mount to <code>/etc/postgresql.conf</code> (directly under <code>/etc/</code>) — <em>not</em> <code>/etc/postgresql/postgresql.conf</code>.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500 text-sm">
        <i data-lucide="shield-alert" class="size-4 text-amber-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
        <div><strong>DATABASE_URL — SSL Mode.</strong> Npgsql tries Kerberos/GSS encryption first; if <code>libgssapi_krb5.so.2</code> is absent in the app container it falls back to <em>no encryption</em>, which <code>pg_hba.conf</code> then rejects (<code>SqlState 28000</code>). Append <code>SSL Mode=Disable;Trust Server Certificate=true</code> to the connection string to skip it.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-body !py-3 flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-l-amber-500 text-sm">
        <i data-lucide="database" class="size-4 text-amber-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0"></i>
        <div><strong>Database creation.</strong> If Postgres fails on first start (e.g. a config error), <code>initdb</code> may finish without creating the <code>POSTGRES_DB</code> database. The image only seeds the DB/role on a <em>fresh</em> data directory — it never re-seeds. Create it manually:
            <div class="mt-2 code-surface px-4 py-2"><code>docker exec -it postgres psql -U &lt;username&gt; -d postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE &lt;database-name&gt;;"</code></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 8 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">8. First-time setup</h2>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code><span class="tok-com"># 1. Create directories</span>
mkdir -p &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/data &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/initdb

<span class="tok-com"># 2. Write postgresql.conf (copy content from section 5)</span>
nano &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/postgresql.conf

<span class="tok-com"># 3. Start Postgres and watch it come up</span>
docker compose up -d postgres
docker compose logs -f postgres

<span class="tok-com"># 4. Create the database if not auto-created</span>
docker exec -it postgres psql -U &lt;username&gt; -d postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE &lt;database-name&gt;;"

<span class="tok-com"># 5. Add subnet to pg_hba.conf and reload</span>
echo "host all all &lt;your-subnet&gt;/24 scram-sha-256" &gt;&gt; &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/data/pgdata/pg_hba.conf
docker exec postgres psql -U &lt;username&gt; -d postgres -c "SELECT pg_reload_conf();"

<span class="tok-com"># 6. Deploy Authly (EF Core migrations apply automatically on boot)</span>
docker compose pull authly
docker compose up -d authly
docker compose logs -f authly</code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 9 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">9. Updating Authly</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">Bump <code>AUTHLY_VERSION</code> in <code>.env</code>, then pull and recreate — your data persists in the bind-mounted Postgres directory.</p>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code>docker compose pull authly
docker compose up -d authly
docker compose logs -f authly</code></div>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 10 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">10. Network</h2>
<div class="card overflow-hidden">
    <div class="overflow-x-auto scroll-thin">
        <table class="table">
            <thead><tr><th>Container</th><th>IP</th><th>Port</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>postgres</code></td><td><code>&lt;postgres-ip&gt;</code></td><td>5432</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>authly</code></td><td><code>&lt;authly-ip&gt;</code></td><td>8080</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>redis</code></td><td><code>&lt;redis-ip&gt;</code></td><td>6379</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>
<p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Postgres is bound to <code>127.0.0.1:5432</code> on the host — <strong>not internet-facing</strong>. Authly is reached externally via Traefik at <code>https://&lt;authly-domain&gt;</code>.</p>

@* ----------------------------------------------------------------- 11 *@
<h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-2">11. Useful commands</h2>
<div class="code-surface px-4 py-3 text-sm"><code><span class="tok-com"># Check Postgres is healthy</span>
docker ps --filter name=postgres --format "table {{.Names}}\t{{.Status}}"

<span class="tok-com"># Connect to Postgres</span>
docker exec -it postgres psql -U &lt;username&gt; -d postgres

<span class="tok-com"># Verify custom config loaded</span>
docker exec -it postgres psql -U &lt;username&gt; -d postgres -c "SHOW shared_buffers;"

<span class="tok-com"># View logs</span>
docker compose logs -f authly
docker compose logs -f postgres

<span class="tok-com"># Backup database</span>
docker exec -t postgres pg_dump -U &lt;username&gt; -d &lt;database-name&gt; -Fc &gt; &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/backup_$(date +%Y%m%d).dump

<span class="tok-com"># Restore database</span>
docker exec -i postgres pg_restore -U &lt;username&gt; -d &lt;database-name&gt; &lt; &lt;base-path&gt;/postgres/backup_YYYYMMDD.dump</code></div>

